description:
Bananas: At Any Cost

Health-Medical Documentary hosted by Juan Dominguez, published by WG Films in 2011 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Bananas: At Any Cost
Juan Accidentes Dominguez is on his biggest case ever. On behalf of twelve Nicaraguan banana workers he is tackling Dole Food in a ground-breaking legal battle for their use of a banned pesticide that was known by the company to cause sterility.
&quot;This film just demonstrates how multi-national organisations go about abusing their positions within society in the quest for money. Sadly the chemicals banned in the developed world are still sold for use in developing countries and it is the poorer people within these countries that suffer. Bananas is a must see and we need more DVD's like this that bring the truth to the world about how their food is really produced, well done film makers.&quot; Harry65.

